-- PRESS DIGEST- Financial Times - July 15
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 08:39PM EDT
-- None



July 15 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories in the Financial Times. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

Headlines  ABBVIE CLOSES IN ON 31 BLN STG TAKEOVER OF SHIRE (http://on.ft.com/1qZO5jA)  CITIGROUP WEATHERS $7 BLN MBS SETTLEMENT (http://on.ft.com/1mbWPNb)  MYLAN IN $5.3 BLN ABBOTT LABORATORIES DEAL (http://on.ft.com/1qByowL)  AIRBUS UNVEILS NEW VERSION OF A330 AIRLINER (http://on.ft.com/1zD7o6g)  CHANGE CAPITAL TO TAKE OVER LUXURY LINENS GROUP FRETTE (http://on.ft.com/1nAhcZI)  Overview  AbbVie <ABBV.N> is close to clinching a 31 billion pound ($52.75 billion) takeover of Shire <SHP.L>, which sells drugs for rare diseases, in what would be the latest example of a U.S. company buying a European rival motivated by tax benefits.  Citigroup Inc <C.N> posted second-quarter earnings that beat analysts' estimates and agreed to pay $7 billion to settle a U.S. government probe into the sale of mortgage-backed securities.   U.S.-based generic drugmaker Mylan said it would pay $5.3 billion for Abbott Laboratories' <ABT.N> generic drugs unit, giving Mylan access to more than 100 generic medicines in developed markets outside of the United States.  Airbus Group <AIR.PA> revealed plans on Monday for a new version of its popular A330 aircraft featuring more fuel-efficient engines, hoping to challenge Boeing Co's <BA.N> dominance in long-range passenger jets.